cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use Ariadne or its findings in academic work, please cite this
  software and the SCADS project deliverable.
title: "Ariadne: Sensemaking for Nonatomic Entities using AI Coding Agents"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Arnaldo
    family-names: Barea
    affiliation: Rochester Institute of Technology
    email: ajb6289@rit.edu
repository-code: "https://github.com/ajbarea/ariadne"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  Modern collection environments produce intelligence about entities embedded
  within large organizational hierarchies stored across highly heterogeneous
  systems — graph databases, structured relational stores, and unstructured
  repositories — spanning metadata, free text, imagery, and video. Ariadne uses
  an agentic AI harness (the Claude Agent SDK) as a unifying analytic interface
  over these diverse environments. Rather than replacing existing infrastructure,
  the harness serves as an orchestration layer that dispatches specialized tools
  and skills to retrieve, interpret, and synthesize information across graph,
  structured, and unstructured sources in a coordinated, multi-hop analytic
  workflow targeting entities within an organizational hierarchy. Developed as
  the umbrella demonstration layer for the SCADS portfolio.
keywords:
  - agentic AI
  - sensemaking
  - entity resolution
  - GraphRAG
  - model context protocol
  - intelligence analysis
  - multimodal reasoning
